# Ansible ad-hac commands

Using Ansible ad-hac commands we can executes commands on remote hosts without manual login.
Ansible establishes an SSH connection with the remote host, executes the command, captures the output and returns it.

Ref : https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/intro_adhoc.html

Setup Ansible lab using  https://github.com/malyabee/vagrant_ansible_lab

"Vagrant_ansible_lab" will provide a 4 node environment (1 management node + 3 targat nodes)


### ad-hac command to display date

ansible node01 -m command -a date
